 programming, in that <br />if some other buggy caller does set things up with an empty range, it gets <br />the right result.<br /><br />Btw, exactly _because_ gcc warnings about uninitialized functions are <br />sometimes bogus (ie due to gcc simply not being able to follow things like <br />conditional initializations where the values are only used if they were <br />initialized), I would ask that people comment on these kinds of issues <br />when they send in patches. <br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
